Subject: Re: [T2] A few questions about our '78

> Hi Jeff,
>
> Probably it is rust and gunk in the fuel system. The inside of the tank
> rusts and flakes, and gets picked up by the fuel filter. As you drive, the
> suction of the system blocks the passage. When you stop, the pressure stops
> and the flakes settle down and allow fuel to pass again. You can probably
> change filters for a bit, but eventually you will need to pull the tank and
> clean and seal it.
>
> Ned
>
> >
> >
